guild raids is not always feasible for many folks with non-trivial RL commitments.  Many of even the &quot;fun&quot; guilds seemed to be oriented toward raids as THE way of bringing members together.  As a result many folks miss out on the opportunity to group with their guildmates because they cannot make it to the raids.  While raids are and will continue to be a fundamental activity for guilds, what follows is a suggestion for a lightweight option for guilds to allow non-raiders in your organizaiton a chance to get together on a regular basis.<br>
<br>
Zone of the Month (ZoM) - The idea behind ZoM is to specify the zones for a particular month (different zones for different levels) where members are encouraged to hang out if they have no better place to go.  During that month casual player members are more likely to find groups of guildmates in those zones for mutual advantage and fun.  No structured activities need be specified although &quot;mini-raids&quot; during the course of the month could be planned for added enjoyment.  ZoM is also a way to spice things up for folks by removing some of the risk of exploring new zones.  <br>
<br>
